title.narrative: OUTPUT 1.4: HEALTH FACILITIES CAPACITIES HAS STRENGHTEN FOR SAM CARE

description.narrative: Health facilities at national, regional and local levels have improved capacities to provide quality treatment to children (6-59 months) affected by SAM, particularly in the areas affected by food insecurity., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 1. By 2022, newborns, children under-five, adolescents, and pregnant and lactating women, increasingly utilize quality health, nutrition HIV and Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) services and families adopt healthy and hygienic behaviours and practices, including during emergencies.

description.narrative: L'UNICEF a réalisé, la révision des documents stratégiques et normatifs à savoir : le Protocole de Prise en Charge de la Malnutrition et la Politique Nationale de Nutrition. L'UNICEF a facilité le lancement de l'Initiative Hôpital Ami des Bébés afin de promouvoir l'Allaitement Maternelle Exclusif au niveau national. Le bureau UNICEF a initié également le lancement du concept « Alimentation du nourrisson et du jeune enfant (ANJE) ». Dans les structures de santé, renforcement de capacité des prestataires de service sur la prise en charge de la malnutrition et suivi par les supervisions du programme de nutrition sur le terrain. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:14/01/2020
